<br>
An email I received today. Names removed as I assume the person wishes to remain anonymous.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
I am a moderately equipped 60 monk from test. I have 2800 hp and 1200 ac unbuffed. I have tested a few encounters after the patch on test.<br>
<br>
I'd like to point out that there was no discernable difference in damage taken(solo) over time from the mobs. I did notice that:<br>
<br>
1. I was taking a lot less hits<br>
<br>
2. When I was getting hit, it would be near to full, or full damage.<br>
<br>
I tried this out on some mobs that were just above light blue con and I actually fared better against them. I pulled some of halls of testing tonight as well. The mobs there hit me quite a bit, as I expected because of there level and attack rating but still seeming to get less, but for damage.<br>
<br>
All in all, I believe this so-called nerf actually helped the soloing monks while slightly diminishing the uber monk tank.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
<br>
Zadkiel. <br>
