-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uuglukson.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uglukson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/10/02 10:32:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11803.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh</span><hr size=1> Unless I am missing something, the only HP slot relevent to the effectiveness of a fungi is the chest slot.  If you can regen more HPs between a CHeal using a fungi than you can have wearing your highest/best other chest slot, then the fungi is the better item in 98% of cases.  The only other times are when added resists, or the added HPs, would prove more useful (when pulling very hard-hitting mobs for example).  The same principle applies for soling - if you regen more over the course of a fight than the HP on your other chest slot item, the fungi will be the superior choice.  Total HPs are irrelevant to the effectiveness of a fungi at any given level.  Sure, if you have higher total HPs, it will take longer to regen you to full, but that's no reason to give up the advantages a fungi provides. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wubao>Wubao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Posts: 1631<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/10/02 11:16:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11803.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> well, let's use soloing as the example</span><hr size=1> Since the fungi is primarily used for soloing, let's look at soloing.<br>
<br>
The GOAL of soloing as a monk: as much XP as fast as possible<br>
<br>
What Fungi brings to the table: Regeneration, decreasing downtime, and allowing you a larger amount of VIRTUAL hit points per fight. Very powerful effect, no doubt.<br>
<br>
What AC brings to the table: Less damage taken over the course of the battle. Unfortunately, this all out of whack once you get past the 40s.<br>
<br>
What DPS brings to the table: Dead mobs. Usually a good thing, since at level 55, handing in Crushbone belts isn't the most efficient way to level.<br>
<br>
What Haste brings to the table: Dead mobs FASTER.<br>
<br>
What HPs bring to the table: You lasting longer, so you can take on more mobs over a shorter period of time or tougher mobs in general.<br>
<br>
Most monks can't take on yellow cons past a certain point of twinkage. So it ends up being dark blue cons.<br>
<br>
Hit points are really good for taking on these dark blue cons, obviously.<br>
<br>
BUT, let's say you can kill say 3 dark blue cons (possibly Sonic Bats as they're a monk favorite) in a row with 1,700 hps before stopping to bandage, and regen up to full.<br>
<br>
Now say you have 2,000 hps when you do this.<br>
<br>
You may be able to squeeze another mob in. You may not depending on the RNG.<br>
<br>
But, your downtime is longer, becauase you've 300 more hps to regen.<br>
<br>
Less EFFICIENT.<br>
<br>
Not less powerful. Not less useful. Less EFFICIENT.<br>
<br>
That's all I was saying.<br>
<br>
Fungi's obviously still the single most powerful item a monk can have for any sort of activity. And the fact that there really aren't many chest items out there with better AC ... it remains end game for a lot of people.<br>
<br>
But, when you start to pile the HPs on, which is what a lot of monks are talking about doing, you do give yourself more time sitting on ye ole butt.<br>
<br>
That's all. Not that big a deal really.<br>
<br>
-Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usssinsssational.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sssin Sssational</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 733<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/11/02 7:40:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11803.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well, let's use soloing as the example</span><hr size=1> So, are we saying that the PSC has NOT notched up at least closer to the uberness of the fungi?  <br>
